Book overview

⚠UPDATED EDITION- AUGUST 2022⚠

♥COMPILATION OF FACTORY AUTOMATION KNOWLEDGE IN A SINGLE BOOK♥


Industrial automation is one of the booming industries nowadays. It is used by many industries to increase their productivity, quality of work and fulfill maximum consumers’ demands. Therefore, the requirement of automation solutions has also increased exponentially in this decade. Also, automation has opened doors to many opportunities for skilled professionals. Due to the increasing demands of skilled professionals, it is necessary for engineers to upgrade their knowledge and skills to meet such requirements.

This book covers

★ Basics of Automation with practical applications

★ Different components of Automation such as Relay, contactor, etc.

★ PID controller

★ Various Digital and Analog sensors

★ PLC control panel

★ PLC communication protocol

★ Basics of PLC

★ PLC programming using Siemens TIA portal V16

★ Pneumatic and Hydraulic systems with cylinder selection criteria

★ Electric motor and gear box

★ Sinamics V20 VFD with its different operating modes.

★ Basics of servo drive with its applications

★ HMI development using TIA Portal V16

★ Basics of SCADA with its different applications

Why this book?

◆ Digestable & practical lessons

◆ Well organized information

◆ In-depth software elaboration

◆Start writing your own program

Suitable for?

◆Students as well as working professionals

◆Individual with basic knowledge of factory automation

♥Grab your copy♥

From the Publisher

Industrial Automation Series

Everything about factory automation

For Beginners

- Lessons on PLC control panel and components

- Lessons on analog and digital sensors

- Basics of PLC programming using Siemens TIA portal

- Lessons on HMI and SCADA

- Lessons on VFD and servo drives

Everything about PLC Programming

For Beginners with basic knowledge of industrial automation

- Lessons on Allen Bradley, Siemens, and Mitsubishi PLCs

- Different PLC programming languages

- Practical examples for better comprehension

Advanced PLC programming Part 1

For beginners with basic knowledge of PLC programming

- Dedicated book on Allen Bradley studio 5000 Logix designer

- Virtual PLC training kit

- Lessons on ladder logic instructions

- Lessons on AB and vendor modules configuration

- Lessons on HMI, Alarms, VFD, Troubleshooting, etc.

Advanced PLC programming Part 2

For professionals with PLC programming knowledge

- Kinetix servo programming

- Vision system

- ABB robots

- Scanner and FTTM

- Anu many more
